   <titleInfo>
      <title>General Orders, Watson B. Smith in Marysville, Tenn. 1863 Nov. 6</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>By command of Brig. Gen. Sanders, Watson B. Smith wrote to Lt. Col. Adams and his regiment (1st Ky Cav.) extending the thanks of Maj. General Burnside for the daring attack they made against the enemy at Motley Island Ford, Little Tennessee River in which they captured thirty-five prisoners and killed many more without loss to themselves. Smith asked that Adams make out a statement and send to the Tribune and to forward the inclosure to Harper.</abstract>
